briefdescription.para: NEW: This event is fired before the page is loaded into memory, and before stored form data is loaded. It may be used, e.g., for authentication, to retrieve/prepare stored data, and/or to control form rendering according to user preferences.

NEW: This event is fired after the page is loaded into memory, before stored form data is loaded, and before the form is visible. For example, It may be used to determine the data to be loaded and to perform the data loading.

NEW: This event is fired after the page is loaded is memory, after the data is loaded into the form, but before the form is displayed. It may be used to perform form activities that are controlled by the loaded data.

briefdescription.para: NEW: A text identifier that is used to group multiple versions of a single form. The lineage is constant for all versions of a single kind of form.

detaileddescription.para: When appended to , it can be used to retrieve all versions of one particular form.

simplesect.para: contains the version text for the current form. It is designed to be used in conjuction with and .

briefdescription.para: NEW: The full URI that uniquely identifies the current form. It is created by concatenating + lineage + version. Each of the componenets is separated by a single forward slash.
NEW: The full URI used to identify the form that is the immediate previous version of the current FormDesign

NEW: Unique URI used to identify a unique instance of a form. Used for tracking form responses across time and across multiple episodes of editing by end-users. This URI does not change for each edit session of a form instance.

NEW: Unique URI used to identify a unique instance of a form's saved responses. It is used for tracking form responses across time and across multiple episodes of editing by end-users. This URI must change for each edit/save session of a form instance. It may be e.g., a new GUID, or a repeat of the formInstanceID followed by a version number.

detaileddescription.para: NEW: Unique URI used to identify a unique instance of a form. Used for tracking form responses across time and across multiple episodes of editing by end-users. This URI must change for each edit session of a form instance.

briefdescription.para: NEW: Unique URI used to identify the immediate previous instance of a form containing responses. This is the that represents the instance of the form that the user opened up before beginning a new cycle of edit/save. This attribute is used for tracking form responses across time and across multiple episodes of editing by end-users. This URI must change for each edit session of a form instance.
